Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:24.30,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the skies that are still unknown to me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.30,0:00:28.40,Default,op,0,0,0,,I know, you're doing just the same -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.40,0:00:29.98,Default,op,0,0,0,,Dreaming
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:35.24,Default,op,0,0,0,,Just a small glow\NFrom those great days
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.24,0:00:38.12,Default,op,0,0,0,,Is what dragging you along
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:41.87,Default,op,0,0,0,,Giving you faith and some comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.87,0:00:45.76,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the sun that scorches badly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:52.13,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only want to see your guise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.13,0:00:53.91,Default,op,0,0,0,,But instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.91,0:00:59.14,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only watch \NWith tears on my face
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.14,0:01:04.74,Default,op,0,0,0,,As you slowly disappear in this noon haze
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.74,0:01:07.75,Default,op,0,0,0,,We're alone \NWe're alone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:11.28,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}Walking this world on our own
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.32,0:01:16.52,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(1000,0)}Looking for each other since long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.52,0:01:22.49,Default,op,0,0,0,,In the end, in the end, \NAfter the day we finally meet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:26.97,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\b1\bord1\blur1\t(2100,2200,\shad3\blur3\c&HABADD8&)}We won't ever have to say "Goodbye"
Comment: 0,0:01:33.06,0:01:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{OP END}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.52,0:01:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,4-1. \NBroir lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, Marchesa Broir clobbers Ryuzaki, \Nleaving her no chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The 14 years old prodigy \Ntwists the Queen of Japanese Amateurs around the finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:15.96,Default,,0,0,88,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&HAC907F&\t(0,1100,\bord0\blur0.55)\c&HFEFEFD&\fnGabriola\fs80\frz360\3a&H2D&}Episode 11 \N\N\N\N{\fs105}It won't fly, anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Todo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.41,0:02:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That fellow is returning later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He has his own matches \Nscheduled throughout January.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to maintain the training pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is keeping herself busy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.41,0:02:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever they go, \Nthey always root for each other. {This one is fucked up with pronouns, who is rooting for who is a sheer guess here}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.94,0:02:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo sure matured, hasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.99,0:02:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. I barely managed to deter him \Nand shove back into the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Living the role, aren't you, Sadist Manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.97,0:02:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Demon, if anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.95,0:02:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure, Demon Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're at it, will you drop by my place now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.54,0:03:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's pretty much what I returned for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.28,0:03:11.49,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Queen's Cup '90 \NThird Round \NQuarterfinals
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.49,0:03:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Round three. Oka played with Natasha Dollis. \NClobbered her with 6-3 and 6-4.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.93,0:03:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But this match was much rougher...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. First match of the third round. \NMarchesa Broir vs. Ryuzaki Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In first set, Broir secured a huge lead of 5-1, \Nforcing Madame Butterfly to metamorphose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Metamorphose?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Not a trace was left \Nof Madame Butterfly's usual lofty play!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was inconceivable, Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You could never tell the girl in front of you \Nwas Madame Butterfly,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.57,0:04:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the one titled the Supreme Queen \Nfor her fierce offense and brilliant footwork!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing the pride away, \Nshe stuck to the baseline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.32,0:04:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,she ceased any offense towards the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Switched to the receive-only strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever chances she had before, \Nshe never locked herself from going forward. {/ in the back / played defensive}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept forbearing and receiving Broir's serves \Nfrom the baseline, all the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.90,0:04:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a novice facing a seasoned opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as though she said, \N"I am not yet adept enough to go offensive!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Desperately staying clear from mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Her focus was on receive, receive and receive only!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After that and till the end of the game, \Nshe never dared to attack even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was perhaps the first time ever \Nanyone saw such a match from Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it yielded a magnificent result.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In Madame Butterfly's battle of attrition, \Nthe composure of callow Broir crumbled soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Against an opponent that refuses to step forward, her attacks became reckless and grueling, wrecking Broir's pace completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Time after time, she was making careless mistakes, \Nultimately ruining herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Out! 7-5, 6-3.\NMatch won by Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki managed to win!\NNow she advances to semifinals!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A win is a win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in order to achieve it, \NMadame Butterfly had to stop being Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But she won after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This stratagem cannot be a universal solution! {This trick won't work indefinetely.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want Madame Butterfly \Nto ever again play a match like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't Madame Butterfly say, she'd prefer to stay an amateur for the rest of her life, to keep playing her own tennis?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't Madame Butterfly choose this \Nto remain Madame Butterfly, regardless of winning and losing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.38,0:06:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She can still keep winning, \Nif such is Madame Butterfly's destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the point - she can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.02,0:06:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There will always be some fresh power that'd defeat her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.39,0:06:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even among the pro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.56,0:06:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But fatal to her, so particular about winning! {No clue what is in that "koubasagata" whisper and after "kodawaru"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Worst of all is that she realizes it herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.74,0:06:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You went through such privations for it, Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.05,0:07:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.36,0:07:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.67,0:07:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really letting me stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.50,0:07:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a match tomorrow, \Nand it's no fun enjoying such a beautiful night view alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The semifinals are here, at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.53,0:07:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, as the grand final is approaching, we announce matchups for Queen's Cup '90 semifinals, held the day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.73,0:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Ling Kowon (China) vs. Oka Hiromi (Park Hill Affiliate)\NJean Ryder (America) vs. Reika Ryuzaki (Park Hill Affiliate)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what kind of player is this Ling Kowon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly is now facing \Nthe tournament's number one favourite Ryder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:40.99,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Jean Ryder              Reika Ryuzaki
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly wins,\Nand Hiromi also wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To make the final dream showdown come true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that, long faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.17,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, take a quick look here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:07:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool, isn't it? \NI learned this one just recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.05,0:08:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly won today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, she did!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Although she won, it feels off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Feels so off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.33,0:08:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations on your advance to semifinals...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.60,0:08:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.47,0:08:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Hiromi. \NYou too do your best in semifinals, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She must have been crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.85,0:08:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would a winner do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.35,0:08:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.82,0:08:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But this was the first time \NI saw Madame Butterfly so lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You're through to the Sealine Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to speak to Mr. Katsura Daigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.86,0:09:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, Mr. Katsura \Nsuddenly checked out at 6 pm today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Although tomorrow night \Nwe expect him to check back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.61,0:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where are you going, Reika?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to ever again \Nfind myself in a match like today's.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I will make sure to show you a brilliant match \Nwith Jean Ryder the day after tomorrow, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.48,0:09:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NHow did Madame B. wander in here, of all people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.40,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hiromi can do it, \Nthere is no way that I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.44,0:10:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When receiving the inbound ball,\Nshe returns it in the lowest point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know she has been trained by the special plan \Nto acquire this technique ever since Coach Munakata's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to use it too. \NI want to carry on his legacy too. {/ I want to be part of it too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot do that.\NIt will ruin your own tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.78,0:10:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, it is already ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.36,0:10:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since this tournament's first round, \Nwhen Hiromi first showed me her brilliant wield of this technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, day by day, Hiromi was asserting \Nher superiority over me, steadily widening that gap between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.31,0:10:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm asleep, when I'm awake, \Nand even when I'm holding the racket in the middle of a match,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.81,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,those thoughts keep haunting me, \Nwhile she becomes less and less visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.85,0:11:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please say it, Coach Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.02,0:11:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That you will do everything you can to help me defeat Jean Ryder, so that in the finals I could stand on the same court as Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.23,0:11:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if my tennis career ends here, \NI want it to be due to facing a mighty opponent like Oka Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.14,0:11:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only if I lose to her,\Nthat I could leave with no regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One more step forward, Madame B!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.02,0:11:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, you still hold back your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You never made more than one step from the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.68,0:11:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this line that you made up yourself to sit on \Nand make a huge step away from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you can pick it up in just a night or two?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For over 20 years, you've been believing \Nin this line you made up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you forgo it, there can be no progress!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not getting anywhere at this rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.65,0:12:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's just one night, \NI have to put a 20 years' worth in it alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You are delirious{/ daydreaming}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.38,0:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when do you let illusions{/ hallucinations} take over you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.59,0:12:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,30-15.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is in good shape. In the semifinal match against Ling Kowon, \NOka scores one return ace after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.47,0:13:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since she entered this tournament, \NOka's strength never ceases to amaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.14,0:13:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,After analyzing Oka's matches in second and third round, \NI finally understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.25,0:13:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to how she played before, \Nshe advanced significantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.77,0:13:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to elaborate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say it's the receiving point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Receiving point?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I never noticed until I looked closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.34,0:13:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to other players, her timing for sending an inbound ball \Nback to the opponent is a few split-seconds earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a bit tricky to explain \Nwithout technical intricacies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Some split-seconds, or about 10 to 20 cm closer to the ground \Nthan the rest of the players - that's where she receives the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.09,0:13:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.73,0:13:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It means such a timing in tennis is beyond common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.35,0:13:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe, \Nbut the more I look, the more I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka was clearly not playing like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.03,0:13:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you omit reporting such a thing to America!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.63,0:14:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to see it yourself in practice first. Both you and Todo. \NYou'd never believe something like this is happening otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.48,0:14:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is advancing to finals, without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, it won't take more than 10 more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.26,0:14:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, is she asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We came home just this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she hasn't slept a wink \Nsince the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.36,0:14:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How peculiar to see her losing composure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa, this child has always been acting that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not every time to this extent, \Nbut always this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.24,0:14:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Although she would never disclose it in front of public, \Nthis child endured more suffering and hard labor than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"It'd be better if she never discovered tennis," \NI had such thoughts numerous times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.09,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosy, affectionate and frolic, making everyone laugh, \Njust the kind of child she was before all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not so. Perhaps, it's not tennis, \Nbut something else that drives her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she worked harder than anyone, \Nand suffered accordingly. But that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, don't you think your daughter \Nis a marvelous person?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.22,0:15:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be watching, \Neach of her first-grade strokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.89,0:15:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell her just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Great work, Oka!\NYou advance to finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Really! She is so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice play!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.95,0:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.79,0:16:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.26,0:16:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Show it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a couple of blisters burst. \NBut nothing serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,An injured hand must be disinfected immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.14,0:16:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.44,0:16:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You already came this far.\NKeep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.67,0:16:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, let's proceed \Nto the second match of semifinals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.16,0:16:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, it's time.\NWake up Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi did win her match, father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. 6-1 and 6-2. \NShe fought spectacularly and advanced to finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.25,0:17:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do my best too, in that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of three set match.\NService play: Ryder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryder seizes the initiative at once, \Nshe is this tournament's final Big Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tournament's number one favourite, Jean Ryder vs. \Nthe Queen of Japanese Amateur Tennis, Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The winner of this game \Nwill then play with Oka in the finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.76,0:17:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,30-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.53,0:17:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{Didn't get the first word. Half-guessed the last one as well}A certain difference in power is apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryder is #7 in world rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Her winning a major Japanese tournament would be no surprise, \Nas she is still a rising player.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Her temper is nothing like Broir's. \NA true seasoned pro!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up, Madame B! \NYou'll never be able to hit like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you manage to perform it once or twice during training, \Nit'll never work in actual match!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well! I'm saying that you'll never surpass Oka, \Nnot because your techniques are inferior.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If we speak techniques, \Nyours are probably a level or two higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But that... That's precisely why you'll never surpass her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.16,0:18:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{Vaguely unsure about 1st 2 words}Your muscle memory bounds you to your own techniques \Nand is certain to always hit the brakes in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.83,0:19:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Too anxious about failure, you can't muster the courage \Nfor half a step more, hitting the brakes instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You constantly retrospect, and the better your tennis is honed, \Nthe more you worry about failing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like many outstanding players, you accustomed your body to playing tennis on reflexes in order to eliminate mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.95,0:19:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You get it now, Madame B?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata picked the untrained Oka \Nand instead of eliminating mistakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.99,0:19:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,made her the only one to take half a step forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He dedicated the whole teaching process to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything. Even what was left of his life. \NHe dedicated everything to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.07,0:19:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why Oka was able to do it \Nand you will never be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Coach Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I will still give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It is indispensable right now to find the courage \Nfor that one step forward, further than I had ever gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just for me standing here, on this court, \Nbut for my entire future! {Not just for me, standing on this court now, but to keep living my life further on!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.16,0:20:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.22,0:20:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I could do it before. \NI managed it so many times during practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.29,0:20:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives it to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:20:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,6-1, 6-0. \NSet count: 2 against 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.86,0:21:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Match won by Ryder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She lost! \NMadame Butterfly has lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's better if I go away?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.60,0:21:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, you have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.67,0:21:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.34,0:21:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NReika cannot fly anymore.
Comment: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED START}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:21.22,Default,ed,0,0,0,,There is one song I cannot ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.22,0:22:26.85,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Still, there's a face I'm willing to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:29.81,Default,ed,0,0,0,,With her feelings mixed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.81,0:22:32.69,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Alice got completely lost
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.69,0:22:37.88,Default,ed,0,0,0,,The midst of summer \NBrought her into one tricky love maze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.20,0:22:44.79,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I want you to hug tightly\NAnd never let go of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.79,0:22:50.17,Default,ed,0,0,0,,One scared and timid tiny girl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.17,0:22:57.05,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I quite remember our very first kiss \NAnd the beginning of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.63,0:23:03.47,Default,ed,0,0,0,,While birds were singing for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.54,0:23:12.66,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I'll take a car and take a lonely trip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:17.86,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I know it'll bring me \NTo the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.86,0:23:20.91,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Where only the the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.91,0:23:23.95,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Dazzlingly bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.95,0:23:29.48,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Could witness my long-awaited happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Aikawa Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Queen's Cup '90 finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.78,0:23:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But this all feels somehow unbelievable - \NHiromi's opponent is sadly not Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.89,0:23:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.45,0:23:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's thanks to Madame Butterfly, \NHiromi could make it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.56,0:23:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be mourning about that, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still here. Still here, you are! \NAnd you should definitely win!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Closing episode: "FINAL STAGE."
